snippet: Seeming weary of requests to explain her third-place finish in the Democratic mayoral primary, Christine C. Quinn turned back to the business of legislating.
abstract: New York City Council Speaker Christine C Quinn turns back to the business of legislating after finishing third in the Democratic mayoral primary; winning just roughly 15 percent of the vote was a disappointment for Quinn, who was long the frontrunner in the race and who received enormous attention as potentially the city's first female and openly gay mayor.
lead_paragraph: Seeming weary of requests to explain her third-place finish in the Democratic mayoral primary, Christine C. Quinn turned back to the business of legislating.

headline.main: Trounced in Primary, Quinn Returns to Council, Seeking the Old Normal
headline.print_headline: Trounced in Primary, Quinn Returns to Council, Seeking the Old Normal
